  <a id="position1"></a>
  <div class="col-md-4">
    <h4 style="margin-top: 40px;">
      LEADERSHIP, OUTREACH, & MARKETING <br>
    </h4>
    <p style="clear:left;">
      This is the most important role at ThinQ.tv. It is your opportunity to be on the ground floor of a movement to create the future of participatory thought-provoking entertainment.<br><br>
      
      Seeking engaging self-starters to host video chat conversations about current events. Successful candidate(s) will gain leadership and community-building skills while moderating exciting live conversations within the context of celebrity news critic shows, such as those hosted by John Oliver, Stephen Colbert, and Hasan Minhaj. It's like going to a cocktail party on Zoom, but you don't have to wait to be invited to discover fascinating conversations with smart people.<br><br>
    </p>

      <p style="font-weight: bold;">Learning Outcomes:</p>
      <p>
        - Leadership skills<br>
        - Teamwork with remote colleagues<br>
        - Effective methods for building online community fellowship
      </p><br>

      <p style="font-weight: bold;">Responsibilities:</p>
      <p>
      - Post 10 hours per week when you will be at a computer (or phone) with a window open to the ThinQ.tv live video viewer<br>
      - Along with other interns, organize and participate in online conversations about TED talks and news critique shows.<br>
      - Reach out to friends and family who are isolated: Get them to participate in video conversations throughout each week.<br>
      - Invite organizations and influencers to join ThinQ.tv conversations.<br>
      - Create social media videos.<br>
      - Arrange podcast speaking engagements for Dr. Schaefer.
      </p><br>

      <p style="font-weight: bold;">Qualifications:</p>
      <p>
      - Demonstrated an ability to accomplish goals through previous academic, volunteer, or work experience<br>
      - Excellent conversational and writing skills
      </p>
